@ThinkingandTinkering - You are putting a restriction/condition upon speech, therefore how can it be considered to be "free"? By definition you do not agree with free speech.

You might not like the way some people talk or how they express themselves. Free speech is there to protect those people from you... 🤣

I do realize however that this is your channel and your rules and you can of course do as you please. Just don't claim to be a free speech advocate while simultaneously explaining how you limit speech.

@ThinkingandTinkering It's not about batteries vs non-batteries. It's about level of information that we can learn from your videos. When it's batteries, there's lots of things we don't know and we learn a lot, that's what we're here for. When you built a wimshurst machine, I learned lots of new things even though I've built my own before, like coating disks with isolating layer to prevent discharge between sectors, adding conductive knobs, etc. 

When you build a sub-optimal wind generator for 5 videos straight or convert a bike into a ghetto generator, there's nothing to learn from it, so no wonder some of us get upset with it.

I also noticed there's a dozen really strange fanboys that just seem extatic about whatever videos you post, regardless of what it is. I actually don't understand them.
